{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6212ad23-7a35-47d1-880c-f43ec4ad3cd0","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 opt-in and is no longer needed.\n\nYou can simply remove that line:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_4WPJePgjQYg1hU1AyBD3Sh","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Wcn6Xv25OlFi5qQY7WYViW","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c8420125c6294ba19dedff3d6c99daf4/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c8420125c6294ba19dedff3d6c99daf4/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"26145e6f-a96c-4258-a1ef-e6e146a5b513","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about native MTP support. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Let me provide the correct guidance.\n\nIn .NET 10:\n- `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively (it's the default).\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed — it was a .NET 9 opt-in mechanism.\n- `EnableMSTestRunner` is still needed to enable the MSTest runner mode (which makes the test project an executable that uses MTP).\n\n\n- So they can simply remove that `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` line from their project file.","outputTokens":485},"id":"2625a85b-f316-471c-b3d1-02fa9a0d1b25","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:49:00.160Z","parentId":"e4de87da-2af1-470f-87bc-478ff8e1a32c"}
